@aliyazdi75 The version of Linux you are using would have been in the first line of the `flutter doctor -v` output, but that line is missing. Which version of Linux do you use?

@helin24 Can you take a look at this?

> @aliyazdi75 The version of Linux you are using would have been in the first line of the `flutter doctor -v` output, but that line is missing. Which version of Linux do you use?

It was there but idk why github removed it. I fixed it.
Thanks for the update, @aliyazdi75. Do you use 200% zoom, like in #6318?

> Thanks for the update, @aliyazdi75. Do you use 200% zoom, like in #6318?

Yes, exactly as same as the mentioned issue.

@aliyazdi75 can you download the Flutter plugin v69 and see if the problem exists there?

If not, it's likely this caused the problem: https://github.com/flutter/flutter-intellij/pull/6283 and I'd revert back to the `OFFSCREEN` rendering mode.
@aliyazdi75 I think you'll need to download 69.0.3, because 69.0.1 is meant for an older version of Android Studio. Sorry, I should have specified the version!
Thanks for checking! I have never been able to reproduce this problem on my system. I'll revert the change I made.
Oops! I just finished uploading the 70.1 point release and it does not include this change. Sorry about that.

title: Inspector opens somewhere else
